OL,3,CFlagship sites to house asylum seekers
OL,4,Ccost millions more than hotels
OL,6,FTo compound matters, hundreds fewer
OL,7,Fmigrants are currently being housed in
OL,8,Fsuch modes of accommodation than first
OL,9,Fplanned.
OL,11,FThe NAO, by the end of March, expects
OL,12,Fthe Home Office to have spent at least
OL,13,F#230 million developing four major
OL,14,Fprojects - the Bibby Stockholm barge
OL,15,Fin Portland, Dorset, the former RAF
OL,16,Fbases at Scampton in Lincolnshire and
OL,17,FWethersfield, in Essex, and ex-student
OL,18,Faccommodation in Huddersfield, West
OL,19,FYorkshire.
