OL,3,CFlagship sites to house asylum seekers
OL,4,Ccost millions more than hotels
OL,6,FHead of the NAO Gareth Davies said:
OL,7,F"The Home Office has made progress in
OL,8,Freducing the use of hotels for asylum
OL,9,Faccommodation.
OL,11,F"Yet the pace at which the government
OL,12,Fpursued its plans led to increased
OL,13,Frisks, and it now expects large sites
OL,14,Fto cost more than using hotel
OL,15,Faccommodation."
